HEADWORD: Chattering
<hw>Chat"ter*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or habit
of talking idly or rapidly, or of making inarticulate sounds; the sounds
so made; noise made by the collision of the teeth; chatter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

